goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of flight distances and the frequency of flights at different distances.

goals.question: Which airports have the most flights?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the busiest airports and the ones that have the most flight connections.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Flight Delays')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median Delay: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    average_delay = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean()
    average_delay = average_delay.reset_index()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(average_delay['origin'], average_delay['delay'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('Average Delay Time for Flights by Origin Airport')
    ax.axhline(average_delay['delay'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Overall Average: {average_delay['delay'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Count the number of flights per origin airport
    flight_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()

    # Create a bar chart of flight count by airport
    ax = flight_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 7), color='blue', legend=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('Which airports have the most flights?')
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date

    flight_counts = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.plot(flight_counts['date'], flight_counts['count'], label='Flight Count')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
